ADF: 0.1

🎯 TASK: Routing engine and rule classifier design context (M3)

📋 CONTEXT:
  - The classifier is Charter's core IP — the thing that makes it more than a format with a CLI
  - It routes rules to positions by triggers and weight, the same mechanism pattern as routing cards to positions by spread topology
  - Input arrives (the rule), context gives it meaning (the routing engine decides which section), pattern match selects the handler (CONSTRAINTS vs ADVISORY vs CONTEXT)
  - The classifier already exists in content-classifier.ts for migration (CLAUDE.md -> ADF); M3 extends it to handle freestanding rule insertion via `charter adf add`
  - Design must grow from the rule-routing decision tree already codified in packages/adf/README.md — that spec is the source of truth

📖 GUIDE [advisory]:
  - Phase 1 of routing (manifest triggers -> module resolution) is stable in manifest.ts
  - Phase 2 of routing (content -> section placement) is stable in content-classifier.ts
  - M3 adds Phase 3: freestanding rule classification without a source heading context
  - The gap: content-classifier.ts uses heading context as a routing signal; `charter adf add --rule` has no heading — it must infer from rule text alone
  - Weight inference: imperative patterns (NEVER/ALWAYS/MUST) -> load-bearing; preference patterns (prefer/should/bias) -> advisory; neutral -> advisory default
  - Module inference: check rule text against ON_DEMAND trigger keywords from manifest, fall back to core.adf
  - Section inference: rules -> CONSTRAINTS or ADVISORY; descriptions -> CONTEXT
  - --auto-route should explain its reasoning (which signals fired, confidence level)
  - --dry-run must preview the full routing decision before writing

⚠ CONSTRAINTS [load-bearing]:
  - Deterministic heuristics first — do not require LLM inference for classification
  - Every new command must support --dry-run --format json
  - Classifier decisions must be explainable: which patterns matched, why this section, why this weight
  - Do not duplicate routing logic — extend content-classifier.ts, don't create a parallel path

📋 CONTEXT:
  - Existing classifier entry points: classifyElement(), buildMigrationPlan()
  - Existing strength detection: imperative/advisory/neutral in markdown-parser.ts
  - Existing trigger matching: isKeywordMatch() with prefix stemming in manifest.ts
  - M3 CLI surface: charter adf add --rule "text" [--weight load-bearing|advisory] [--section CONSTRAINTS|ADVISORY|CONTEXT] [--module core.adf] [--auto-route] [--dry-run]
  - Explicit flags (--weight, --section, --module) override auto-route inference
  - Roadmap reference: papers/adf-vnext-roadmap-v0.1.md Milestone 3
